# Per-finding exclusions for gitleaks. Each line is a fingerprint
# `<commit>:<file>:<rule>:<line>`. Used to silence false positives
# already in the immutable git history without forcing a rewrite.
#
# The HTML-REPORT smoke-test heredoc shipped a fixed-hex placeholder
# under `api_key` in the 0.5.23 docs (commit 99bab44). Gitleaks
# treats any high-entropy 16-char value under that key as a leaked
# credential. The value was documentation-only, never deployed, but
# the historical commits cannot be rewritten without force-push to
# main. Subsequent commits replace the placeholder with a runtime-
# generated `$(openssl rand -hex 16)` so future scans stay clean.
99bab44070b3593a3bae24521f8ea7817ca665f8:docs/HTML-REPORT.md:generic-api-key:207
99bab44070b3593a3bae24521f8ea7817ca665f8:docs/FR/HTML-REPORT-FR.md:generic-api-key:214
# The first attempt at silencing the above two findings inlined the
# offending placeholder string in this file's comment, which the
# scanner then flagged as a third leak. The current commit replaces
# the comment with a non-literal description.
897ad89bf9eea37e407742b21d0b5e6afd31d93e:.gitleaksignore:generic-api-key:6
